<div1 type="letter">
<note type="curatorial">5</note>
<opener><salute>Dear Dr. Neihardt,</salute></opener>
<p>I have not heard from you after my letter of a few months ago, and I hope that everything is all right. I had hoped to get to Missouri to visit you this summer but other plans made this impossible. I have promised Adele that we will get there as soon as possible so we can sit and reminisce about the west again. Being so far east al the things that you talked about seem as if they are part of another world so that every now and then I read the Cycle of the West Again to bring the whole story back to the present.</p>
<p>Is there any possiblility of your coming East in the near future? Are you still teaching full time at the University or have you made other plans for next semester. If it is not too much trouble, please write and let me know how you are.</p>

<closer><salute>Fondly,</salute>
	<signed>Bob</signed></closer>

</div1>

